In my view, we use the term God too loosely. There are Mahatma=
s, great Mahatmas, fantastic spiritual beings, and then there is God. Buddh=
a was a fantastic and super-duper spiritual being.

Now coming to your ques=
tion, there is no fixed rule of how and what can lead a man to liberation o=
r higher states of spirituality. Frankly, there is no path which *guarantee=
s* liberation. All paths have the potential, but realization is an individu=
al's journey, and each such journey will not be a mirror of anyone else's j=
ourney. Broadly there may be similarities, but nuances will differ. For som=
e it is necessary to leave their wife and children to be spiritual, for oth=
ers they may not need to do so. 

Infact, the aim of sadhana is to prepare =
yourself. If and when you experience and realize God, it is going be God's =
sweet will. Sadhana does not guarantee realization, but without sadhana it =
is nearly impossibly, for you are simply not prepared enough to experience.=
 

