ends on what we understand by the term spirituality. Many have this notion =
that spirituality only means sitting and doing tough penances ETC. There is=
 more to spirituality than that. Essentially, it is a transformation of min=
d, emotions and body (this bit is nearly impossible) into another state. 

=
Sadhana is needed to prepare the ground - mind/emotions/body. But *meeting =
God* (as you put it) depends on what you mean by God, and on God's sweet wi=
ll. Sometimes, living your daily life with an internal sense of surrender t=
o a Supreme, trying to inculcate equanimity in testing circumstances, tryin=
g to stop the mind from automatically reacting to provocations, seeing othe=
r people's point of views and thus becoming more objective, trying to be co=
mpassionate (but not self-pity or pity in any form, for pity is a degenerat=
ive emotion, while compassion is uplifting) ETC are all sadhanas which can =
be done by anybody. One need not read complex scriptures, or believe in rel=
igion to be able to do these. 

