 - to the Gopis, he was amazed to see that the Gopis would spend the whole =
day doing whatever they must do, but they would perform every action, even =
the most mundane like clearing the garbage, with a small prayer in their li=
ps, "Sri KrishNaaya Samarpayami..". 

Patience and surrender to God can be =
inculcated, progressively, in any life situation. Infact, it is the ONLY th=
ing that you can work on. Rest, the world around apart from you, will follo=
w its own rhythm which has been decided by actions performed in the past wh=
ich one may or maynot be aware of. 

Every blockage is an opportunity to in=
crease the sense of surrender to something Higher, and that in turn acts as=
 a powerful internal catalyst for change.

